metadata.indicator_name: Population that has thought about migrating to another country by age groups
metadata.data_features: Estimates based on opinion surveys conducted by the Latinobar√≥metro Corporation.
metadata.definition: Percentage of the population aged over 18 who has thought about moving to another country to live.
metadata.calculation_methodology: It is calculated dividing the number of people aged over 18 who have seriously consider the idea of going to live abroad, among the total population of the same age group. The result is multiplied by 100.
